main event: A witness observed an unidentified object over W. Carrollton, Ohio on July 7, 1967 at around 10:23 PM.
interesting points: The object appeared to resemble a star in motion and disappeared from view after about 2 minutes of observation.
The witness estimated the object was traveling at a high speed in a northwest direction.
The witness was unable to estimate the distance or speed of the object.
The object did not make any sound and did not leave any trail or vapor.
The witness described the object as having a light and dark appearance.
sighted object: an unidentified object resembling a star
